+======================================================+
|          DRSP (Data Reader SCSA PSI/O)               |
|  (Punched Card Interface & Binary Conversion Logic)  |
+======================================================+

| ----------------- A. PHYSICAL INTERFACE (Card Input) ------------------
|
|  [PUNCHED CARD SLOT] 
|  (Input Media: Represents 8 data positions)
|
+------------------------------------------------------+
|                                                      |
|  8x MECHANICAL/OPTICAL SENSORS (To detect holes)     |
|  (Converts physical hole/no-hole to electrical signal)
+------------------------------------------------------+

| ----------------- B. INTERFACE REGISTRY (Input Latch) ------------------
|
| +--------------------------------------------------+
| |  INPUT LATCH / REGISTER (8 D-Flip-Flops)         |
| |  (Temporarily holds the 8-bit instruction read   |
| |   from the sensors before sending to the CPU/RAM) |
| +--------------------------------------------------+
|
|  - Load_Enable: Signal from CU to latch the data.
|  - Ready_Flag: 1-bit signal to CU (Data is ready).
+----------------------+-----------------------------+

| ----------------- C. OUTPUT BUS INTERFACE --------------------------
|
|                      |
|                      |
| +--------------------+----------------------------+
| |  OUTPUT BUFFER/DRIVER (Tri-State Buffers)       |
| |  (Connects the 8-bit Latch to the System Bus)   |
| +--------------------+----------------------------+
|
|   DATA BUS (1-bit Line)  <-- Controlled by the CPU to read data serially
|   ADDRESS BUS (4-bit)    <-- Not used directly by DRSP, but used to map the DRSP's 
|                              input data to specific RAM locations during loading.

